VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT ServerCertificateValidationCallback\s*?\(.*?(\=|false|true)
WHEN EXPR MISSING:test|development|localhost|staging|// intentional
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects insecure configuration of the ServerCertificateValidationCallback, which may lead to improper validation of server certificates.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Server Certificate Validation: Insecure Configuration.
